frus:attachment.p:
May 5, 1882, at 9 o’clock in the morning, the condemned: 1, Mentor
                            Nicholas; 2, Mathurin Lys; 3, Elogie Guillouette; 4, Maurille Lafontant.
                            5, Klenor Hyacinthe; 6, Petion Avin; 7, Achille Jules, surnamed Lamay;
                            8, Jean Baptiste Codio; 9, Succès fils; 10, Charles Duquéné Fournier;
                            11, Georges Haenuens; 12, Charles Alexis Potavin Gresseau; 13, Alexis
                            Loulon; 14, Prosper Bellanton, were executed publicly at St. Marc.
